<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">The results in Fig. 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F4" class="xref">4</xref> and Table 
 <xref rid="T1" ref-type="table" class="xref">1</xref> show that 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">Ph.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">muscorum</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> spent significantly less time sheltering than either of the two other species under the highest moisture conditions. It also had the steepest gradient for its moisture reaction norm of -2.16, compared with values of -1.05 for 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">A.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">vulgare</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> and -0.19 for 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">P.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">scaber</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> (Table 
 <xref rid="T1" ref-type="table" class="xref">1</xref>). 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">Porcellio</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">scaber</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> showed the least change in the proportion of time it spent sheltering because it sheltered for more than 95% of the time under all substrate moisture conditions. In contrast 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">A.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">vulgare</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name" class="named-content">
   <named-content content-type="genus" class="named-content">Ph.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species" class="named-content">muscorum</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> sheltered for 74% and 51% respectively of the time under the moistest conditions (Table 
 <xref rid="T1" ref-type="table" class="xref">1</xref>).
</p>
